title: All Hallow’s Eve eve at Trackside
text:
All Hallow’s Eve eve at Trackside Oct 20, 2015 Two Birds One Stone plays acoustic rock, classic to modern. 
Rockland — Two Birds One Stone will return to Trackside Station, 4 Union St., for an All Hallow's Eve Party Friday night, Oct. 30. The show will start at 6 p.m. during dinner and drinks. There is no cover charge; costumes are not required, but welcomed. 
Two Birds One Stone is a Midcoast acoustic duo featuring Bret Shepard and Don Joray. They play a diverse mix of classic rock, modern rock, pop and a bit of country. For more information, check out the duo’s Facebook page .
